\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes mandatory requirements for managing logical access to Elko County Information Technology (IT) resources.
 It implements the principles of "Least Privilege" and "Need-to-Know" to protect the confidentiality,
 integrity,
 and availability of County information.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy shall apply to all individuals—
including employees,
 elected officials,
 contractors,
 and third-party vendors—
who require logical access to Elko County information systems,
 networks,
 or data.
 This scope encompasses all systems used to process,
 store,
 or transmit CJI and sensitive County assets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the Access Control Authority;
 validates identity management architectures and adjudicates all policy exceptions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure all access controls for CJI-processing systems meet federal mandates.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
IT Administrators
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall provision,
 modify,
 and disable accounts strictly upon receipt of authorized triggers from Human Resources or Data Owners.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Human Resources (HR)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall act as the Authoritative Source for identity verification and shall provide immediate notification of personnel status changes to the IT Department.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads / Data Owners
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall define the specific "need-to-know" for staff and verify that access requests are commensurate with assigned job duties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall complete periodic access recertification reviews for systems under their data ownership within the cadence defined in Section 6.9 and shall promptly notify the IT Department of any access that is no longer justified.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mandatory Compliance
\series default
:
 Compliance is mandatory.
 Prohibited actions include 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Credential sharing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Unauthorized elevation of privileges
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Bypassing access controls
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Sanctions
\series default
:
 Violations shall result in immediate revocation of access and disciplinary action up to and including discharge,
 consistent with NRS 205.4765.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Any deviation from this policy shall be documented as a formal Risk Acceptance with identified compensating controls and an expiration date not exceeding 12 months.
 Exceptions affecting CJI systems require written approval from the CSO.
\end_layout

