\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1.
 Account Management
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Department shall define and manage account types for each system,
 including at minimum:
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
individual
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
privileged
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
shared/group (restricted)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
service
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
system
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
guest (restricted)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
temporary
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
emergency.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Department shall disable information system accounts within the following maximum timeframes upon notification of a trigger:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Termination or Transfer
\series default
:
 Within 24 hours of notification from Human Resources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
High-Risk Individuals
\series default
:
 Within 30 minutes of discovery for individuals posing a direct threat to CJI.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Expired or Unauthorized Accounts
\series default
:
 Within seven (7) calendar days of account expiration or discovery that an account is no longer associated with an active user.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Inactivity
\series default
:
 The information system shall automatically disable accounts after 30 calendar days of inactivity.
 This standard exceeds the CJIS minimum of 90 days and is adopted as a stricter Elko County internal control.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Information Operations shall manage identifiers (usernames) such that identifiers shall not be reused for a minimum of one (1) year following the disablement or removal of the previous account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shared and group accounts are prohibited unless a documented operational necessity is approved by the IT Director.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
When shared or group account membership changes,
 the associated authenticators (passwords) shall be changed within 24 hours.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Temporary and emergency accounts shall be automatically removed or disabled within 72 hours of creation unless a longer window is approved as an exception.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2.
 Separation of Duties
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Department shall separate duties to reduce the risk of fraud or malevolent activity without collusion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Personnel administering access controls shall not be the same individuals administering the audit functions for those systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Where staffing constraints prevent technical separation,
 compensating controls—
such as independent administrative review—
shall be documented and approved by the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3.
 Least Privilege
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Access shall be restricted to the minimum privileges required for assigned job duties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Privileged accounts shall be used strictly for administrative functions and shall not be used for routine activities such as email or general web browsing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The information system shall prevent non-privileged users from executing privileged functions,
 including the disablement or circumvention of security safeguards.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4.
 Unsuccessful Logon Attempts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
To prevent brute-force attacks,
 the information system shall enforce a limit of 
\series bold
five (5)
\series default
 consecutive invalid logon attempts within a 15-minute period.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
For systems processing CJI,
 accounts shall remain locked until released by an authorized administrator.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Automatic unlock is prohibited for CJI systems unless approved by the CSO for a documented operational mission need.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5.
 System Use Notification
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Before granting access,
 the information system shall display a notification banner stating:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Users are accessing a restricted Elko County / FBI CJIS information system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
System usage may be monitored,
 recorded,
 and subject to audit.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Unauthorized use is prohibited and subject to criminal/civil penalties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Use of the system indicates consent to monitoring with no expectation of privacy.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The banner shall remain on screen until the user takes an explicit action to acknowledge the notice.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6.
 Device Lock and Session Management
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The information system shall automatically initiate a device lock after 15 minutes of inactivity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The lock shall conceal previously visible information with a pattern-hiding display.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Remote access sessions that authenticate via password shall automatically terminate or require re-authentication after twelve (12) hours of duration or 15 minutes of inactivity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Remote access sessions that authenticate via certificate (mobile data terminals) are exempt from VPN inactivity timeouts for officer safety.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Remote access sessions utilizing certificate-based authentication on devices located within a secure Criminal Justice Conveyance (e.g.,
 patrol vehicles) are exempt from the 15-minute VPN inactivity timeout to ensure officer safety.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7.
 Remote Access
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All remote access to Elko County information systems shall be authorized,
 monitored,
 and routed through a County-managed access control point (VPN).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA),
 compliant with CJIS Advanced Authentication standards,
 is mandatory for all remote access and all privileged access.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Remote access communications shall be protected using FIPS 140-validated cryptographic modules.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8.
 Wireless Access
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Wireless access to the internal network must be explicitly authorized and shall use WPA2/3 Enterprise authentication and encryption.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Guest wireless networks shall be logically and/or physically separated from any environment processing CJI or sensitive County data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.9.
 Periodic Access Recertification
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
To ensure access privileges remain commensurate with assigned duties and current business need,
 the IT Department shall conduct periodic access recertification reviews.
 Data Owners shall validate that personnel under their authority retain a legitimate need-to-know for the access granted.
 IT Administrators shall disable or modify accounts where the Data Owner cannot confirm continued business need.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Restricted Systems (Level 4)
\series default
:
 Access to systems processing,
 storing,
 or transmitting Criminal Justice Information (CJI) or other Restricted data (as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
) shall be recertified at least quarterly.
 This cadence aligns with the quarterly risk assessment review cycle for CJI and Critical systems defined in Policy 1.09.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Confidential Systems (Level 3)
\series default
:
 Access to systems storing or processing Confidential data shall be recertified at least semi-annually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Internal Use and Public Systems (Levels 1–2)
\series default
:
 Access shall be recertified at least annually,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AC-6(7).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Privileged Accounts
\series default
:
 All privileged access (Tier L3 and above) shall be recertified at least semi-annually,
 regardless of system classification,
 to validate continued operational need and compliance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 competency maintenance requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Recertification Triggers
\series default
:
 In addition to the scheduled cadence,
 an access recertification review shall be initiated within five (5) business days following a significant organizational change (e.g.,
 departmental reorganization,
 system migration,
 or material change to a Data Owner's scope),
 consistent with NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5:
 AC-2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Documentation
\series default
:
 Recertification results shall be documented in the Department's designated system of record.
 Accounts not recertified within the required timeframe shall be suspended until the review is completed.
 Recertification records shall be retained in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and applicable Nevada retention schedules.
\end_layout

